# 2. Array Methods

JavaScript provides many built-in methods that simplify array manipulation.

---

## push()

Adds one or more elements to the end of an array.

```javascript
fruits.push("Apple");
```

**Returns:** New length of the array.

---

## pop()

Removes the last element from the array.

```javascript
fruits.pop();
```

**Returns:** Removed element.

---

## shift()

Removes the first element.

```javascript
fruits.shift();
```

---

## unshift()

Adds one or more elements at the beginning.

```javascript
fruits.unshift("Orange");
```

---

## splice()

Adds, removes, or replaces elements.

```javascript
numbers.splice(2,1);
```

---

## slice()

Returns a copy of a selected portion of the array without changing the original array.

```javascript
numbers.slice(1,4);
```

---

## concat()

Combines two or more arrays.

```javascript
array1.concat(array2);
```

---

## includes()

Checks whether an element exists.

Returns either **true** or **false**.

---

## indexOf()

Returns the first occurrence of an element.

Returns **-1** if not found.

---

## reverse()

Reverses the order of elements.

---

## sort()

Sorts the elements.

By default, sorting is alphabetical.

---

## map()

Creates a new array by applying a function to every element.

Used extensively in React and modern JavaScript development.

---

## filter()

Creates a new array containing only the elements that satisfy a condition.

---

## reduce()

Combines all elements into a single value.

Commonly used for:

* Sum
* Average
* Maximum
* Minimum

---

## forEach()

Executes a function once for every array element.

Unlike map(), it does not return a new array.

---

## some()

Returns **true** if at least one element satisfies a condition.

---

## every()

Returns **true** only if all elements satisfy a condition.

---

## find()

Returns the first matching element.

---

## findIndex()

Returns the index of the first matching element.

---

## Applications of Array Methods

* Data filtering
* Data transformation
* Searching
* Sorting
* API response processing
* Dashboard development
* Report generation

